{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:18:11.650219+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e3436acc64554d493edbc3b272c249ccf27ee703)", "id": "lc_151b9b56-d4ec-4771-b8da-d369d4a46392"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# pull official base image\nFROM python:3.9-slim-bullseye\n\n# set work directory\nWORKDIR /usr/src/app\n\n# set environment variables\nENV PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE 1\nENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED 1\n\n# install necessary packages\nRUN apt-get update \\\n    && apt-get -y install build-essential \\\n    && apt-get -y install libpq-dev gcc \\\n    && apt-get -y install netcat\n\nCOPY . .\n# install pipenv and project dependencies\nRUN pip install pipenv\nRUN pipenv install --system --deploy --ignore-pipfile", "id": "lc_c2f3a152-4980-4d35-869b-7192780f2fda"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "180970e8-346d-4be6-a584-0547e8e21938", "tool_call_id": "call_2699742addbe44a985c566f2", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:18:29.763251+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a complete picture. Here's the full explanation:\n\n---\n\n## How Application Settings Are Derived from Environment Variables\n\nThis template uses a **centralized `Settings` class** in `app/settings.py` that reads environment variables via `os.environ.get()` and derives all application configuration from them. The environment variables are injected at runtime through a `.env` file (loaded by Docker Compose via `env_file: ./.env`).\n\n### 1. Database URLs (PostgreSQL)\n\nThe individual Postgres credentials come from five separate environment variables:\n\n| Environment Variable | Setting Attribute | Example Value |\n|---|---|---|\n| `POSTGRES_USER` | `DB_USER` | `sasori` |\n| `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` | `DB_PASSWORD` | `sasori` |\n| `POSTGRES_DB` | `DB_DB` | `akatsuki` |\n| `POSTGRES_PORT` | `DB_PORT` | `5432` |\n| `POSTGRES_HOST` | `DB_HOST` | `postgres` |\n\nThese are then **composed into two SQLAlchemy connection URLs**:\n\n- **Main DB URL:**\n  ```\n  DB_URL = f\"postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{DB_DB}\"\n  ```\n  → `postgresql+psycopg2://sasori:sasori@postgres:5432/akatsuki`\n\n- **Test DB URL** (using `POSTGRES_TEST_DB`):\n  ```\n  TEST_DB_URL = f\"postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{TEST_DB}\"\n  ```\n  → `postgresql+psycopg2://sasori:sasori@postgres:5432/hebi`\n\nThese URLs are consumed in `app/db.py`, which creates both an async `Database` connection and a synchronous SQLAlchemy `engine` (with `pool_size=3, max_overflow=0`), and automatically creates the database if it doesn't exist.\n\n### 2. Token & Auth Settings\n\nThe **JWT/token** settings are **hardcoded** in the `Settings` class (not pulled from environment variables):\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `SECRET_KEY` | `environ.get(\"SECRET_KEY\")` → `\"meandyouaretogether\"` | Signing key for JWT encoding |\n| `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME` | `60 * 30` = **1800 seconds** (30 min) | Access token lifetime |\n| `REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME` | `60 * 24 * 365` = **525,600 seconds** (1 year) | Refresh token lifetime |\n| `JWT_ALGORITHM` | `\"HS256\"` | JWT signing algorithm |\n| `PASSWORD_HASHER` | `CryptContext(schemes=[\"bcrypt\"])` | Password hashing (bcrypt) |\n\nOnly `SECRET_KEY` comes from an environment variable. The expiry times and algorithm are constants. The `create_auth_token()` function in `auth/services.py` uses these to encode payloads:\n```python\njwt.encode(data_to_encode, settings.SECRET_KEY, settings.JWT_ALGORITHM)\n```\n\n### 3. Redis Configuration\n\nTwo environment variables map directly to Redis settings:\n\n| Environment Variable | Setting Attribute | Default | Example Value |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `REDIS_HOST` | `REDIS_HOST` | `\"localhost\"` | `redis` |\n| `REDIS_PORT` | `REDIS_PORT` | `\"6379\"` | `6379` |\n\nNotably, Redis defaults to `localhost:6379` if the env vars aren't set (unlike Postgres which has no defaults and would fail). However, in the current codebase, **Redis settings are declared but not yet wired into any application logic** — they're available on `settings.REDIS_HOST` and `settings.REDIS_PORT` for future use (e.g., caching, rate limiting, or session storage).\n\n### 4. Other Application Settings\n\n| Environment Variable | Setting | Transformation |\n|---|---|---|\n| `ALLOWED_HOST` | `ALLOWED_HOST` | Direct passthrough (string) |\n| `DEBUG` | `DEBUG` | Wrapped in `bool()` — note: `bool(\"False\")` is still `True` |\n| `PORT` | `ALLOWED_PORT` | Cast to `int()` |\n\nThese are used in `main.py` to configure the Uvicorn server:\n```python\nuvicorn.run(app=\"main:app\", host=settings.ALLOWED_HOST, debug=settings.DEBUG, port=settings.ALLOWED_PORT)\n```\n\n### Summary of the Data Flow\n\n```\n.env file (or env vars)\n    ↓\nDocker Compose (env_file: ./.env)\n    ↓\nos.environ.get() calls in Settings class\n    ↓\nComposed into DB_URL / TEST_DB_URL (f-string concatenation)\n    ↓\nConsumed by app/db.py (SQLAlchemy engine), auth/services.py (JWT), main.py (Uvicorn)\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1088, "prompt_tokens": 10048, "total_tokens": 11136, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 12, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9536, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0012036096, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002570496, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00094656}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863491-2UtTQqim3w2wfYMm56J0", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3bc-5e42-7a22-9a40-1312ecd2cb57-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10048, "output_tokens": 1088, "total_tokens": 11136, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9536}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 12}}}}]}}}
